<subSubSection id="C30D654BFFA3FF879A3BFB68F82A35FF" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA836C0FFA3FF879A3BFB68F82A35FF" blockId="50.[151,1437,1178,1998]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFA3FF879A3BFB68F94A34B1" bold="true" box="[582,779,1178,1204]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Whitebait Smelt</emphasis>
. To 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF879B3CFB69F9DC34B0" box="[833,925,1179,1205]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.29" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="cm" value="22.9">22.9 cm</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF879BD2FB69F99C34B3" box="[943,989,1179,1206]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="in" value="9.0">9 in</quantity>
) TL (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFA3FF879C62FB69FF5134B0" author="Miller and Lea" box="[1055,1296,1179,1205]" firstAuthor="Miller" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref302113" refString="Miller, D. J. &amp; Lea, R. N. (1972) Guide to the coastal marine fishes of California. California Department of Fish and Game Fish Bulletin, 157." type="book" year="1972">Miller and Lea 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Vancouver Island, British Columbia (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFA3FF879988FB4DF8B534DC" author="Pietsch and Orr" box="[501,756,1215,1241]" firstAuthor="Pietsch" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref312479" refString="Pietsch, T. W. &amp; Orr, J. W. (2019) Fishes of the Salish Sea. University of Washington Press, Seattle." type="book" year="2019">Pietsch and Orr 2019</bibRefCitation>
) to southern California (
<geoCoordinate id="EE235007FFA3FF879C65FB4DFE3A34DC" box="[1048,1147,1215,1241]" degrees="34" direction="north" minutes="24" orientation="latitude" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" precision="925" value="34.4">34°24’N</geoCoordinate>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFA3FF879CEBFB4DFFD034DC" author="Bradburn" box="[1174,1425,1215,1241]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Bradburn" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref265491" refString="Bradburn, M. J., Keller, A. A. &amp; Horness, B. H. (2011) The 2003 to 2008 U. S. West Coast bottom trawl surveys of groundfish resources off Washington, Oregon, and California: estimates of distribution, abundance, length, and age composition. National Marine Fisheries Service Technical Memorandum, NMFS-NWFSC- 114." type="book" year="2011">
Bradburn 
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFA3FF879D70FB4DFF0B34DC" box="[1293,1354,1215,1241]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
). Eschmeyer and Herald also list a questionable record from 
<collectingCountry id="F3007650FFA3FF879B07FB11F9B234F8" box="[890,1011,1251,1277]" name="Saint Pierre and Miquelon" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">San Pedro</collectingCountry>
, southern California. Depth: shallow water to 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF879954FAF4FB303524" box="[297,369,1286,1313]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="495.0">495 m</quantity>
(
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF8799FDFAF5FB9A3527" box="[384,475,1287,1314]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.949952" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="ft" value="1624.0">1,624 ft</quantity>
) (min.: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B31FFA3FF879A48FAF5F9663524" author="Pietsch and Orr" box="[565,807,1287,1313]" firstAuthor="Pietsch" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" refId="ref312479" refString="Pietsch, T. W. &amp; Orr, J. W. (2019) Fishes of the Salish Sea. University of Washington Press, Seattle." type="book" year="2019">Pietsch and Orr 2019</bibRefCitation>
; max.: NWFSC-FRAM). Although the maximum depth record comes from a bottom trawl catch, thus raising the question of whether that fish entered the net in the midwater during deployment and retrieval, we note that there are many bottom trawl catch records from between 300 (
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF879882FA81FB04358B" box="[255,325,1395,1422]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.999232" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="ft" value="984.0">984 ft</quantity>
) and 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF8799FEFA80FB8B3588" box="[387,458,1394,1421]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="495.0">495 m</quantity>
in the DFO and NWFSC-FRAM databases. Thus the maximum depth record of 
<quantity id="4CEF9B25FFA3FF879D28FA80FFDD3588" box="[1365,1436,1394,1421]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.95" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" unit="m" value="495.0">495 m</quantity>
seems reasonable. An “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFA3FF8799B3FA65F88035B4" baseAuthorityName="Ayres" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[462,705,1431,1457]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Osmeridae" genus="Allosmerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osmeriformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFA3FF8799B3FA65F88035B4" box="[462,705,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Allosmerus elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” from Bristol Bay, Alaska (Personal communication: University of Washington, Burke Museum of Natural History and Culture Fish Collection, Seattle, Washington) is an 
<taxonomicName id="4C174D43FFA3FF8798BBFA2DFB1135FC" box="[198,336,1503,1529]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Osmeridae" genus="Osmerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Osmeriformes" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B963EAD2FFA3FF8798BBFA2DFB6B35FC" box="[198,298,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Osmerus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(Katherine Maslenikov).
</paragraph>
